org.checkerframework.checker.nullness

Class NullnessStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.checkerframework.framework.flow.CFAbstractStore<V,S>
      • org.checkerframework.checker.initialization.InitializationStore<NullnessValue,NullnessStore>
        • org.checkerframework.checker.nullness.NullnessStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Store<NullnessStore>, org.plumelib.util.UniqueId

    public class NullnessStore
extends InitializationStore<NullnessValue,NullnessStore>
    Behaves like InitializationStore, but additionally tracks whether PolyNull is known to be NonNull or Nullable (or not known to be either).

      • leastUpperBound

        public NullnessStore leastUpperBound(NullnessStore other)
        Description copied from interface: Store
        Compute the least upper bound of two stores.

        Important: This method must fulfill the following contract:

        • Does not change this.
        • Does not change other.
        • Returns a fresh object which is not aliased yet.
        • Returns an object of the same (dynamic) type as this, even if the signature is more permissive.
        • Is commutative.
        Specified by:

      • supersetOf

        protected boolean supersetOf(CFAbstractStore<NullnessValue,NullnessStore> o)
        Description copied from class: CFAbstractStore
        Returns true iff this CFAbstractStore contains a superset of the map entries of the argument CFAbstractStore. Note that we test the entry keys and values by Java equality, not by any subtype relationship. This method is used primarily to simplify the equals predicate.
